        # ReleaseNotes of this module
        ReleaseNotes = 'What''s New in v1.0.21

ENHANCEMENTS

iLO Connection - User-Configurable Retry Parameters
• Connect-HPEGLDeviceComputeiLOtoCOM: Added 3 new retry control parameters - MaxConnectionAttempts (1-30, default 10), ConnectionRetryDelaySeconds (1-60, default 5), ConnectionMonitoringTimeoutSeconds (30-600, default 120)
• Benefits: Flexible retry behavior for different network environments, fast-fail mode for testing, extended resilience for unreliable networks
• Fully backward compatible with existing scripts (defaults match previous hardcoded values)

API Wrapper Functions - Collection Property Detection
• Invoke-HPEGLWebRequest & Invoke-HPECOMWebRequest: Synchronized collection property detection logic across both wrappers
• Enhanced detection for non-standard property names (items, roles, users, members, resources, data)
• Added metadata property exclusion (excluded, count, total, offset, limit) to prevent false matches
• Ensures consistent behavior across all HPEGL* and HPECOM* cmdlets

Server Utilization & Sustainability Insights - Bug Fixes & Improvements
• Get-HPECOMSustainabilityInsights: Fixed server-specific query bug - single server queries now correctly filter instead of returning all servers (added resource-uri parameter support with productId+serialNumber format)
• Get-HPECOMServerUtilizationInsights: Fixed data processing bug - single-server utilization queries now correctly extract items from API response
• Get-HPECOMServerUtilizationInsights: Enhanced non-Intel server handling - no longer blocks upfront, API determines compatibility with processor-specific guidance in warnings
• Both cmdlets: Fixed WhatIf issues - no longer show false "No data found" warnings during API preview
• Build Process: Streamlined validation (~200 lines removed) for improved efficiency

Technical Improvements:
• Enhanced query construction with resource-uri for precise server filtering
• Improved pagination handling with SkipPaginationParameters for resource-uri queries
• Fixed data wrapping issue when using ReturnFullObject flag
• Enhanced items array extraction logic for all utilization metric types


INSTALLATION
Install-Module -Name HPECOMCmdlets -Force
Update-Module -Name HPECOMCmdlets

Requirements: PowerShell 7.0+, HPE GreenLake with COM service
